        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3395789801" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16802932654041993379">Most of the stories in this collection didn&apos;t do much for me. I&apos;m definitely more of a fan of Willis&apos; time-travel fiction (the title story is set in the same universe as DOMESDAY BOOK and TO SAY NOTHING OF THE DOG) than her &quot;straight&quot; SF and other genres (disaster, ghost story, humor, etc). Although all of these stories were originally published between 1979 and 1984, a number of them have a much older feel. High 2 stars.</span>
  <span id="freeText16802932654041993379" style="display:none">Most of the stories in this collection didn't do much for me. I'm definitely more of a fan of Willis' time-travel fiction (the title story is set in the same universe as DOMESDAY BOOK and TO SAY NOTHING OF THE DOG) than her "straight" SF and other genres (disaster, ghost story, humor, etc). Although all of these stories were originally published between 1979 and 1984, a number of them have a much older feel. High 2 stars.</span>
